<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith (2005) indicated that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent article (Smith, 2056) showed that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
When the author is referred to more than once in the same paragraph do not include the date in 
subsequent references, as long as the work cannot be confused with others cited.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	In a recent article, Smith (2056) showed that&hellip; Smith also found that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	In his article &#34;Something went wrong&#34;, Smith (2056) revealed that &#34;pilot error was 
	most likely the cause&#34; (p. 4).
	<br>
	Alternatively: &#34;Pilot error was most likely the cause&#34; (Smith, 2056, p. 4).
</blockquote>
